Pope Tawadros II attributed the priests of Ain Shams in the departure of Father Bishoy Aziz
05 Nov 2019, 09:06 by Sameh Salam
His Holiness Pope Tawadros II, Pope of Alexandria, Patriarch of the Holy See of Saint Mark, offered his condolences to the Congregation of the Priests of the Churches of Ain Shams at the passing away of Father Bishoy Aziz, the priest of the Martyr Mar Mina Church and the Angel in a thousand dwellings. Father Bishoy Aziz Younan, the priest of the Church of the Martyr Mar Mina, and the angel in the thousand dwellings, passed away at the age of 73, after 33 years of priestly service. He was born in El Fashn, Beni Suef governorate, on July 4, 1946.He graduated from the Faculty of Engineering, Ain Shams University, Waseem, a priest on March 6, 1987, and received Qumsiya on March 17, 2017. The opportunity to take a last farewell look, as the mass is to be prayed tomorrow morning to begin the funeral prayers at eleven in the morning;
